The course was excellent. No complaints. I would have preferred to be directed to take the courses in order. The videos are great. A little more reading would be a nice break from the routine. Flags for terms and words of value are to be auto-added to notes. Or a notepad filled with important terms and words would be nice. Everyone isn't accustomed to or able to take quality notes. Often they are the difference maker when preparing for tests or certifications.

It's a very good introductory course not just to some of the Azure offerings, but to Data terms in general. I've used databases since at least 1998 and even with that experience I have learned valuable information with this course. This course is good for you, whether you use Azure or not (of course is even better if you do use Azure), so you can't be wrong.The presentation and aesthetics of this course are some of the best I have seen in Coursera, and I have seen a lot of courses here, so congratulations to the builders of this course!
